Аноним 12/08/23 Суб 23:03:47 № 453839 375
Сисы...

Claude 2 uses a more memory-efficient passage retriever to break up contexts into relevant passages. This allows fitting more total tokens into memory.

The core Claude 2 transformer model itself still has a 4096 token limit. But with the retriever, it can provide summaries/passages from documents up to 100k tokens.

So in practice, Claude 2 can consume documents with 100k+ tokens, but only processes 4096 tokens through its transformer at a time by selecting the most relevant passages.
